@NODE "INTRO_DEF" "Cosmetic.guide/INTRO_DEF"
@TITLE "Cosmetic - Introduction"

   Cosmetic
   ~~~~~~~~
   Cosmetic is a combination of MagicWB-deamon and MagicCopper. For the time
   being it won't have a gui but I'll probably create one in some time. This
   small but powerfull utility allows v39+/AGA users to have mwb-pens and a
   lovely copper on any screen without having their memory reduced ,like the
   MagicWB-deamon does, which steals about 300k!. This program is also public
   domain and I don't want any fees from you, altough a nice postcard would be
   appreciated.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "INTRO_SYSREQ" "Cosmetic.guide/INTRO_SYSREQ"
@TITLE "Cosmetic - System Requirements"

   System Requirements
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   First of all you need an Amiga equipped with OS3+ (v39+) this is because
   pen matching/allocating was introduced in v39. You'll also need an AGA-
   equipped machine or something that supports AGA-copperlists. If you don't
   have an AGA machine but do have v39 then you'll get a 8-bit colorcopper list.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "INTRO_USE" "Cosmetic.guide/INTRO_USE"
@TITLE "Cosmetic - Installation"

   Installation
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~
   Copy the program called 'Cosmetic' to your c: directory and add the
   following 3 lines to your s:user-startup :

   ;BEGIN Cosmetic
   run <>NIL: c:Cosmetic
   ;END Cosmetic

   To set Cosmetic to the preferences you want you should read the next
   part.

   Using
   ~~~~~
   All options are parsed with ReadArgs() with the following template:

   "CS=CopperStart,CE=CopperEnd,CP=CopperPen/N,PS=PubScreen/K,NP=NoMWBPens/S,NC=NoCopper/S,NoMWB=NoAllocMWB/S,NoCop=NoAllocCopper/S"

   where

   CopperStart    = Copper Starting Color format RRGGBB.(hex)
   CopperEnd      = Copper Ending Color format RRGGBB (hex).
   CopperPen      = Pen to add copper to.
   PubScreen      = Public screen to do set the MWB Pens and/or create the copper on.
   NoMWBPens      = Turn MagicWB-deamon pen allocation&setting off.
   NoCopper       = Turn Copper off.
   NoAllocMWB     = Don't try to allocate the pens for the MagicWB pens, simply steal them.
   NoAllocCopper  = Don't try to allocate the pen for the copper, simply steal it.

   Using both NoMWBPens and NoCopper will automagicaly exit the program because it won't
   have anything to do.

   The RRGGBB means the following :

     RR = Red quantity
     GG = Green quantity
     BB = Blue quantity

   all ranging from 0 till 255 in hex thus 00 till ff.
   Some colors are:

     000000 - black     ff00ff - purple
     ffffff - white     ffff00 - yellow
     ff0000 - red       ffaa00 - orange
     00ff00 - green     aaaaaa - gray
     0000ff - blue

   You can easily create a color by using the most palette tools.

   Cosmetic can be removed from your system by sending a break command to it's process.
   So firstly find its process number by executing 'status' then execute 'break <number>'.
   
   Examples (put these in your user-startup or run them from a cli):

   o Start with 100% green&1/256 blue, ending in 1/256 red&100% blue, add copper
     to the color best matching the default (blue==00f), allocate & set MagicWB pens :
     Cosmetic ff0001 0100ff

   o Start with black, end in white, add copper to pen 8 don't allocate&set MwbPens :
     Cosmetic 000000 ffffff 8 NoMwb

   o Allocate & set MagicWB pens, don't add a copper :
     Cosmetic NoCopper

   o Allocate & set MagicWB pens on pubscreen 'BigScreen.1', and add default copper
     to pen 11 but don't allocate a copperpen or mwbpens :
     Cosmetic PubScreen="BigScreen.1" CP=11 NoAllocCopper NoAllocMwb


@ENDNODE

@NODE "MISC_UPDATES" "Cosmetic.guide/MISC_UPDATES"
@TITLE "Cosmetic - Updates"

   Updates
   ~~~~~~~
   Whenever a new release of Cosmetic gets released, I will post some
   information in the appropriate newsgroups of some electronic networks.
   The new archive will soon be available on many bulletin boards and on
   all `AmiNet' FTP servers. You will be able to find Cosmetic on the Aminet
   in util/wb.


@ENDNODE

